{
  "stem": "4753.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I never could see him again, because-- I am cutting way ahead myself-- but after the war, he was taken during the war to the Russian front.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when the war came almost to the end, he was taken to Yugoslavia by the German SS to work in a copper mine as a Jewish soldier.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was between them-- you know, one part of the mine blew up.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were taking out the Jewish young soldiers and walked-- marched somewhere.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know the place.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But that is recorded in the history.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And had to dig their own grave, and he was shot into that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But he was the last few who was shot into their grave.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when darkness came, he climbed out from the grave and ran away.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "A Yugoslav woman found him collapsed, took him in, and nursed him for three days.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My brother himself took out the two bullets of himself with a pen knife.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But German SS men came from house to house in that place looking for food and found my brother there and took him to a concentration camp, to Germany.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So you see, they knew they lost the war, meaning the Germans, but to kill, still, that was the most important thing for them-- to kill the Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he took him to Germany.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I don't know the date when, but he was liberated.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he returned to Hungary looking for us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he didn't find anyone.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then he was asked to join the Communist Party.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my brother did find out a lot of things what was going on in the city before we were taken away, and-- and so on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the very same people who were the greatest Nazis became the greatest communists.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
